cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.MM

The paper deals with the vulnerability of mobile authentication systems to shoulder surfing attacks, which is a security and privacy concern. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects, such as hand position and observation angle, which suggests the possibility of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a secondary category. Additionally, the paper involves video recordings and online experiments, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper deals with mobile devices, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
